  "texts": [
    "GenAI models, such as Generative Adversarial Networks (GANs) and Variational Autoencoders (VAEs) [2], demonstrate this capability across various domains, from image generation to text.",
    "Generative models can mimic distribution of real datasets, a principle that's equally valuable in generating coherent and contextually relevant dialogue [3].",
    "For dialogue systems, the generative aspect allows to produce responses that can adapt to the flow of conversation.LLMs such as GPT (Generative Pre-trained Transformer) and BERT (Bidirectional Encoder Representations from Transformers) have revolutionized the field of natural language processing (NLP) by providing deep contextual understanding.",
    "These models are trained on vast corpora of text, enabling them to grasp and generate human-like text.",
    "The Transformer model is the architecture behind many LLMs, which employs self-attention mechanisms to understand the context within text sequences [4]."
  ],
